Hi Intra.<br>
<br>
As far as I understand it this spell range does raise your effective casting level but ONLY with regard to fizzle rates so might be best used for the following situations:<br>
<br>
1. On someone who just gained a new spell rank. Spells tend to fizzle more when you first get them and this is only partially due to needing a higher casting skill. I vaguely remember a developer posting a while back that there is an extra fizzle modifier factored in when you try to cast a spell at the level you recieved it, although I don't know if this modifier diminishes as you advance beyond the minimum casting level.<br>
<br>
2. Casting practice, especially for those skills that won't max themselves through normal play or that lag behind because the class doesn't get a spell of that type during the early levels. e.g. Evocation for Enchanters, Conjuration for Wizards.<br>
<br>
Personally I found it not worth the effort for normal grouping situations although I can see how it might benefit Hybrids who are more likely to come under the second category (this was especially true for Beastlords and Evocation until recently).<br>
